HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1426
By Raper
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Owen Clemons of
Cleveland High School upon his remarkable
success as an athlete and student.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize and
commend those successful high school students who, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Owen Clemons of Cleveland High School,
an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who not only has proven himself a
formidable competitor on the track but a distinguished student and community leader, as well;
and
WHEREAS, Mr. Clemons has established himself as one of Tennessee's elite distance
runners through his exceptional accomplishments in cross country and track and field; and
WHEREAS, a three-time State champion, Mr. Clemons has achieved remarkable
performances, including a 14:39 5K and 4:04 in the 1,600-meter race, placing him among the
top high school runners in the entire nation; and
WHEREAS, Owen Clemons maintains a 4.0 grade point average while balancing the
demands of high-level training and competition, demonstrating outstanding discipline as an
athlete and a student; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of his talent and dedication, Mr. Clemons has committed to
continue his academic and athletic career at Northern Arizona University, widely regarded as
one of the premier collegiate programs in the country for distance running due to its
championship culture, high-altitude training environment, and consistent development of elite
athletes; and
HJR1426
017859
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mr. Clemons has exhibited athleticism and ambition that surely bode well
for his future success as a Division I athlete and a marketing student; and
WHEREAS, Owen Clemons's noteworthy achievements are a tremendous source of
pride for his family, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Clemons is known for his humility, strong character, and leadership, and
he remains grounded in his Christian faith, giving God all the glory for his success; and
WHEREAS, his dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of our respect, admiration,
and commendation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Owen Clemons of Cleveland High School upon
his remarkable success as an athlete and student of the highest caliber and extend to him our
best wishes for much continued success and happiness in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
